Module 3: Language Features
  Introduction
  Constants
    const declaration creates a read-only reference to a value
    const variable needs to be initialied at declaration
    let has block-Scope
    eg. 
      if(true) {
        let cardId = 100;
      } 
      console.log(cardId);
      
  let and var for Variable Declarations
  Rest Parameters
  Destructuring Arrays
